701183f.title: Bronx: Grand Concourse - 193rd Street (East)
701183f.text:
Grand Concourse, north from East 193rd Street (left), to East Kingsbridge Road, showing W.P.A. workmen repaving the thoroughfare. In
the background appears Poe Park.
March 31, 1936.
Works Progress Administration.
Federal Art Project photo.

701182f-a.title: Bronx: Grand Concourse - 193rd Street (East)
701182f-a.text:
2615 Grand Concourse, adjoining the S.W. corner of East 193rd
Street, showing the home of Francis Eeil.
About 1913.
